        @{"     " link Tools.IconEdit        } IconEdit
        @{"     " link Tools.InitPrinter     } InitPrinter
        @{"     " link Tools.KeyShow         } KeyShow
        @{"     " link Tools.Lacer           } Lacer
        @{"     " link Tools.MEmacs          } MEmacs
        @{"     " link Tools.PrepCard        } PrepCard
        @{"     " link Tools.PrintFiles      } PrintFiles
        @{"     " link Tools.ShowConfig      } ShowConfig

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.Calc "Calc"
@version 2.145
@toc Workbench.Tools

    Calc


            This tool allows addition, subtraction, multiplication, and
        division of numbers in a graphical interface. The results of
        operations are displayed in the top of the window, similar to
        a real calculator. The following gadgets are available:

            0 to 9      Enters a digit corresponding the that particular
                        gadget, in the range of 0 to 9.

            .           Enters a decimal point, used in floating point
                        arithmatic.

            +-          Changes the sign of the value to either + or -.

            +           Adds the current value to the next value entered.

            -           Subtracts the current value to the next value
                        entered.

            *           Multiplies the current value to the next value
                        entered.

            /           Divides the current value to the next value entered.

            =           Provides a total of all previously entered operations
                        since it was last cleared.

            CA          Clears all previous entries.

            CE          Clears only the current entry.

            <-          Removes the digit last typed in the upper window.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.CMD "CMD"
@version 2.138
@toc Workbench.Tools

    CMD


            This tool allows the operating system to redirect printer
        output to a file. This program is useful for systems that do
        not have a printer connected.

            DEVICE=     The hardware device port to redirect output
                        from. This may be set to PARALLEL or SERIAL.
                        Any output sent to the specified device will
                        be saved to a file.

            FILE=       The path and name of the file to have output
                        redirected to.

            SKIP=       Sets whether the initial sequence to the device
                        will be redirected or ignored.

            MULTIPLE=   Allows more than one program to have its output
                        redirected.

            NOTIFY=     Allows this tool to display progress messages.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.GraphicDump "GraphicDump"
@version 2.149
@toc Workbench.Tools

    GraphicDump


            This program is used to output screen images to your printer.
        First you must setup the printer's specifications using the Printer
        preference programs on the Workbench disk. The printer must have
        an appropriate driver and must be capable of printing graphics.
        After a short delay, the image of the frontmost screen will be
        printed. The GraphicDump tool supports one tooltype.

            SIZE=       Specifies the size of the printed image. May be
                        set to TINY, SMALL, MEDIUM, or LARGE. May also
                        be used to specify specific sizes by entering
                        the number of horizontal pixels, a colon, and the
                        number of vertical pixels (i.e. SIZE=640:400).

@endnode
