@node HDToolBox.Partition "Partition Drive"
@version 2.154
@toc Tools.HDToolBox

    Partition Drive

        Delete Partition        Used to delete the current partition highlighted
                                in black on the status bar at the top of the
                                Partitioning window.

        New Partition           Used to add a new partition in an unused
                                portion of the status bar at the top of the
                                Partitioning window.

        Default Setup           Creates a default setup in the status bar, and
                                selects a file system appropriate for your
                                system.

        Help                    Displays online help for using the Partitioning
                                options. Explains how to change the size of
                                the partitions and how to preserve them.

        Advanced Options        Used to display the Advanced Options listed
                                below.


    Advanced Options

        Start Cylinder          Specifies the starting cylinder of the
                                current partition.

        End Cylinder            Specifies the end cylinder of the
                                current partition.

        Total Cylinder          Specifies the total cylinders of the
                                current partition.

        Buffers                 Specifies the number of buffers used by
                                the current partition.

        Partition Device Name   Specifies the device name assigned to
                                the partition. This is different than the
                                Volume name.

        File System             Specifies the file system to be used. For
                                more information, see the Change option
                                in the File System list below.

        HostID                  ID used to recognize the drive by.

        Bootable                Specifies whether the drive may be booted
                                off of.

        Boot Priority           Specifies the boot priority in determining
                                which drive in the system will be booted
                                if a disk is available.


    File System

        @{"     " link Partition.Change           } Change
        @{"     " link Partition.Update           } Add/Update

@endnode
