@node Tools.InitPrinter "InitPrinter"
@version 2.149
@toc Workbench.Tools

    InitPrinter


            This tool sends an initialization sequence to the printer.
        The printer preferences may be set using the Printer preferences
        program on the Workbench disk. The printer must be on in order
        for the initialization to be sent properly.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.KeyShow "KeyShow"
@version 2.154
@toc Workbench.Tools

    KeyShow


            This tool shows how each key of the standard keyboard is used.
        Some keys are normal alphanumeric keys, while others are control
        keys or special modifier keys.

            Qualifier keys include CTRL, SHIFT, and ALT. These are often
        held down while pressing another key or combination of keys to
        produce a desired character or control code. Characters are often
        displayed on the screen while control codes are often intercepted
        by the window or program and used to perform a predetermined
        function.
            Keys shown in boldface-italics are affected by the dead-keys.
        These keys may be used to create various accents such as used by
        various languages. The dead keys are shown in blue when the ALT
        key of KeyShow is depressed. To display a special character with a
        dead key, press ALT and the dead key, and then press the normal
        key. For example, to display č press ALT-G followed by the letter E.
        Č may be displayed by pressing ALT-G followed by SHIFT-E. A list of
        these special dead keys and accentable keys are listed in the Index.

            Alternate character sets may be displayed by either pressing
        the CTRL, SHIFT, or ALT keys on the keyboard while the KeyShow
        window is active, or by selecting the gadgets in the KeyShow window
        with the mouse.

@endnode
