@node Tools.PrintFiles "PrintFiles"
@version 2.149
@toc Workbench.Tools

    PrintFiles


            This tool is used to print documents to your printer. In order
        to print one or more documents, you must first select the icons
        of the documents you wish to print. Then, while keeping the icons
        selected, double-click on the PrintFiles icon. This will send the
        documents to the printer for printing. The following tooltype is
        supported.

            FLAGS=FORMFEED      Specifies that each new file is to begin
                                printing on a new page. Otherwise, if
                                multiple files are printed, the beginning
                                of the next file will be printed on the
                                same page as the previous file.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Tools.ShowConfig "ShowConfig"
@version 2.149
@toc Workbench.Tools

    ShowConfig


            This tool is used to display information about the computer.
        This includes the main processors, custom chips, Kickstart
        revisions, memory locations, and expansion boards.

            PROCESSOR       Includes the CPU, FPU, and MMU, if available.
                            Will not report clock speeds.

            CUSTOM CHIPS    Reports the type of chip set such as OCS, ECS,
                            or AGA, the video display mode such as NTSC
                            or PAL, and special chips such as the ECS Agnus
                            or ECS Denise.

            VERS            Reports the version of the Kickstart, Exec, and
                            the Workbench Disk. The Kickstart is generally
                            stored in ROM and the Workbench is generally
                            stored on disk.

            RAM             Reports the type of RAM, its location, and the
                            amount of RAM available. This will not include
                            RAM that has been used to store a Kickstart
                            image, such as on a softkicked A3000.

            BOARDS          Reports information regarding an expansion
                            boards available to the system, such as the
                            ID number, manufacturer, and RAM access
                            locations.

@endnode
