@node Workbench.WBStartup "WBStartup"
@version 2.142
@toc Workbench
@prev Workbench.Utilities

    WBStartup


            The WBStartup drawer contains programs and utilities that are
        loaded whenever the Workbench is loaded with the LoadWB command.
        For most users this occurs while booting the system. Each file
        executed must contain an icon and an associated executable file.

            Any icon in the WBStartup drawer may use one of the following
        ToolTypes.

            DONOTWAIT   This forces the Workbench to open a tool without
                        waiting for another tool to be completed.

            WAIT=       Specifies the number of seconds the Workbench
                        will wait before the next icon in the WBStartup
                        will be executed.

            STARTPRI=   Specifies the priority used to determine the
                        order for which tools in the WBStartup are to
                        be executed. Tools with higher priorities will
                        be executed first.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


